{"title_page": "Sudama Setu", "text_new": "{{Infobox bridge\n| name                = Sudama Setu\n| native_name         = \u0ab8\u0ac1\u0aa6\u0abe\u0aae\u0abe \u0ab8\u0ac7\u0aa4\u0ac1\n| native_name_lang    = gu\n| image               = Sudhama setu.jpg\n| image_upright       =\n| alt                 =\n| caption             = The bridge connects the temple and island\n<!---| map_type    = India Gujarat\n| map_relief  = yes--->\n| coordinates         = {{coord|22|14|12|N|68|58|7|E|region:IN-GJ_type:landmark|display=inline,title}}\n| carries             = pedestrians\n| crosses             = Gomti river\n| locale              = [[Dwarka]], Gujarat, India\n| official_name       =\n| other_name          =\n| named_for           = [[Sudama]]\n| owner               =\n| maint               =\n| heritage            =\n| id                  =\n| id_type             =\n| website             =\n| preceded            =\n| followed            =\n| design              = [[pedestrian bridge|Pedestrian]] [[suspension bridge]]\n| material            = Concrete\n| material1           = Steel\n| material2           =\n| length              = {{Convert|166|m|ft|0|abbr=on}}<ref name=\"DeshGujxx2016\"/> \n| width               = {{Convert|4.2|m|ft|0|abbr=on}}<ref name=\"DeshGujxx2016\"/> \n| height              =\n| depth               =\n| traversable         =\n| towpath             =\n| mainspan            =\n| number_spans        =\n| piers_in_water      = 2\n| load                =\n| clearance_above     =\n| clearance_below     =\n| life                =\n| architect           =\n| designer            =\n| contracted_designer =\n| winner              =\n| engineering         =PKS Infra Engineers Pvt. Ltd{{cn|date=February 2016}}\n| builder             = [[Reliance Industries Limited]]\n| fabricator          =\n| begin               = 5 May 2011\n| complete            = February 2016\n| cost                = {{INRConvert|7.42|c}}<ref name=\"DeshGujxx2016\"/> \n| open                =\n| inaugurated         ={{start date|11 June 2016}}<ref name=\"DeshGujxx2016\"/>\n| rebuilt             =\n| collapsed           =\n| closed              =\n| replaces            =\n| traffic             =\n| toll                =\n| mapframe_zoom = 14\n}}\n'''Sudama Setu''' is a [[pedestrian bridge|pedestrian]] [[suspension bridge]] in [[Dwarka]], [[Gujarat]], India. It is named for [[Sudama]], a childhood friend of [[Krishna]].<ref name=\"PN2015\">{{cite web | author=[[Parimal Nathwani]] | title=Janmashtami and Teacher\u2019s Day Coincides:  Who could be bigger teacher than Krishna? | website=DeshGujarat | date=5 September 2015 | url=http://DeshGujarat.Com/2015/09/05/janmashtami-and-teachers-day-coincides-who-could-be-bigger-teacher-than-krishna/ | accessdate=10 October 2015}}</ref>\n\n==Construction==\nA pedestrian bridge over Gomti river connects [[Dwarkadheesh temple, Gujrat|Jagat Mandir]] of mainland Dwarka and Panchnad or Panchkui Tirth on the island in southeast of it. The bridge was proposed in 2005 to boost tourism on the island. The island has religious as well archaeological significance. There are five sweet water wells called Panchkui associated with five [[Pandava]] brothers of ''[[Mahabharata]]''. Gomti river was crossed by boats until construction of the bridge.<ref name=\"DeshGujaratk2008\">{{cite web | author=DeshGujarat | title=Suspension bridge to link Dwarka and Panchkua island | website=DeshGujarat | date=30 October 2008  | url=http://DeshGujarat.Com/2008/10/30/suspension-bridge-to-link-dwarka-and-panchkua-island/ | accessdate=21 June 2015}}</ref><ref name=\"The Times of Indiak2010\">{{cite web | title=Soon Sudama Setu to connect island to Dwarka temple | website=The Times of India | date=25 June 2010  | url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/rajkot/Soon-Sudama-Setu-to-connect-island-to-Dwarka-temple/articleshow/6089792.cms | accessdate=8 July 2015}}</ref><ref name=\"Indiax2015\">{{cite web | author=India | title=\u2018Sudama setu\u2019 connecting Dwarka with Panchnad likely to be completed before &#91;sic&#93; Janmashtami festival | website=The Indian Express | date=20 June 2015 | url=http://indianexpress.com/article/india/india-others/sudama-setu-connecting-dwarka-with-panchnad-likely-to-be-completed-befor-janmashtami-festival/ | accessdate=21 June 2015}}</ref><ref name=\"dna 2010\">{{cite web | title=Sudama Setu to connect more tourists to Dwarka | website=dna | date=25 June 2010  | url=http://www.dnaindia.com/india/report-sudama-setu-to-connect-more-tourists-to-dwarka-1401014 | accessdate=21 June 2015}}</ref> As Jagat Mandir is an [[Archaeological Survey of India]] (ASI) protected site, permission was needed for construction of the bridge. The Vadodara circle of ASI gave a nod to the bridge in 2008.<ref name=\"DeshGujaratk2008\"/><ref name=\"Indian Express\">{{cite web | title=Suspension bridge to Dwarka gets ASI nod | website=Indian Express | url=http://archive.indianexpress.com/news/suspension-bridge-to-dwarka-gets-asi-nod/377356/ | accessdate=2015-06-21}}</ref> The ground breaking ceremony for the bridge was held on 5 May 2011 by Gujarat Tourism minister [[Jaynarayan Vyas]] and Rajya Sabha MP [[Parimal Nathwani]].<ref name=\"DeshGujarat 2011\">{{cite web | author=DeshGujarat | title=Rs. 9.5 crore Sudama setu project kicks off in Dwarka | website=DeshGujarat | date=5 May 2011  | url=http://DeshGujarat.Com/2011/05/05/rs-9-5-crore-sudama-setu-project-kicks-off-in-dwarka/ | accessdate=21 June 2015}}</ref> Construction of the bridge was delayed due to ASI Delhi not granting the permit until 2013.<ref name=\"www.divyabhaskar.co.in 2013\">{{cite web | title=\u0aa6\u0acd\u0ab5\u0abe\u0ab0\u0a95\u0abe\u0aa8\u0ac0 \u0ab8\u0ac1\u0aa6\u0abe\u0aae\u0abe \u0ab8\u0ac7\u0aa4\u0ac1 \u0aaf\u0acb\u0a9c\u0aa8\u0abe \u0a85\u0aa7\u0acd\u0aa7\u0ab0\u0aa4\u0abe\u0ab2, \u0aa7\u0acb\u0ab7\u0aa3\u0abe \u0aaa\u0acb\u0a95\u0ab3 \u0ab8\u0abe\u0aac\u0abf\u0aa4 \u0aa5\u0a87 | website=www.divyabhaskar.co.in | date=30 May 2013  | url=http://www.divyabhaskar.co.in/news-fb/SAU-JAMN-no-stat-work-on-sudama-setu-plan-4278566-PHO.html | language=gu | accessdate=21 June 2015}}</ref><ref name=\"DeshGujaratbb2011\">{{cite web | author=DeshGujarat | title=Pending ASI approval delaying Sudama Setu project | website=DeshGujarat | date=13 October 2011  | url=http://DeshGujarat.Com/2011/10/13/pending-asi-approval-delaying-sudama-setu-project/ | language=la | accessdate=21 June 2015}}</ref> The bridge was completed in February 2016.<ref name=\"PTI 2016\">{{cite web | author=PTI | title=Construction of 'Sudama Setu' completed in Gujarat | website=The Economic Times | date=1 March 2016 | url=http://economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/economy/infrastructure/construction-of-sudama-setu-completed-in-gujarat/articleshow/51209137.cms | accessdate=5 April 2016}}</ref><ref name=\"Indiax2015\"/><ref name=\"DeshGujarat 2015\">{{cite web | author=DeshGujarat | title=Sudama Setu bridge in Dwarka by July 2015: Minister in Assembly | website=DeshGujarat | date=24 March 2015  | url=http://DeshGujarat.Com/2015/03/24/sudama-setu-bridge-in-dwarka-by-july-2015-minister-in-assembly/ | accessdate=21 June 2015}}</ref><ref name=\"Desh2015\">{{cite web | author=DeshGujarat | title=In photos: Construction of Dwarka Sudama setu almost complete | website=DeshGujarat | date=21 August 2015 | url=http://DeshGujarat.Com/2015/08/21/in-photos-construction-of-dwarka-sudama-setu-almost-complete/ | accessdate=1 September 2015}}</ref>\n\n[[Reliance Industries Limited]], in collaboration with the Gujarat Tourism Department and Gujarat Pavitra Yatradham Vikas Board, built the bridge.<ref name=\"Indiax2015\"/> The bridge cost {{INRConvert|7.42|c}}. It is named for [[Sudama]], a childhood friend of [[Krishna]].<ref name=\"Indiax2015\"/> The bridge is 166 meters long and 4.2 meters wide, having the capacity to carry 25,000 to 30,000 pedestrians an hour.<ref name=\"Indiax2015\"/><ref name=\"DeshGujxx2016\">{{cite web | title=Chief Minister Anandiben Patel Inaugurates \u2018Sudama Setu\u2019 at Dwarka | website=DeshGujarat News from Gujarat | date=11 June 2016 | url=http://deshgujarat.com/2016/06/11/chief-minister-anandiben-patel-inaugurates-sudamasetu-at-dwarka/ | accessdate=23 October 2016}}</ref> The bridge is constructed with 40mm locked coil cable ropes provided by Usha Martin Limited.<ref name=\"Usha Martin 2013\">{{cite web | title=Usha Martin\u2019s bridge cables in Sudama Setu, a cable suspension bridge in Gujarat | website=Usha Martin | date=15 January 2013 | url=http://www.ushamartin.com/news/usha-martins-bridge-cables-in-sudama-setu-a-cable-suspension-bridge-in-gujarat/ | accessdate=10 October 2015}}</ref>\n\nThe bridge was inaugurated by Gujarat Chief Minister [[Anandiben Patel]] on 11 June 2016.<ref name=\"DeshGujxx2016\"/>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n[[Category:Devbhoomi Dwarka district]]\n[[Category:Pedestrian bridges in India]]\n[[Category:Bridges in Gujarat]]\n[[Category:Suspension bridges in India]]\n[[Category:Bridges completed in 2015]]\n[[Category:2015 establishments in India]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox bridge\n| name                = Sudama Setu\n| native_name         = \u0ab8\u0ac1\u0aa6\u0abe\u0aae\u0abe \u0ab8\u0ac7\u0aa4\u0ac1\n| native_name_lang    = gu\n| image               = Sudhama setu.jpg\n| image_upright       =\n| alt                 =\n| caption             = The bridge connects the temple and island\n<!---| map_type    = India Gujarat\n| map_relief  = yes--->\n| coordinates         = {{coord|22|14|12|N|68|58|7|E|region:IN-GJ_type:landmark|display=inline,title}}\n| carries             = pedestrians\n| crosses             = Gomti river\n| locale              = [[Dwarka]], Gujarat, India\n| official_name       =\n| other_name          =\n| named_for           = [[Sudama]]\n| owner               =\n| maint               =\n| heritage            =\n| id                  =\n| id_type             =\n| website             =\n| preceded            =\n| followed            =\n| design              = [[pedestrian bridge|Pedestrian]] [[suspension bridge]]\n| material            = Concrete\n| material1           = Steel\n| material2           =\n| length              = {{Convert|166|m|ft|0|abbr=on}}<ref name=\"DeshGujxx2016\"/> \n| width               = {{Convert|4.2|m|ft|0|abbr=on}}<ref name=\"DeshGujxx2016\"/> \n| height              =\n| depth               =\n| traversable         =\n| towpath             =\n| mainspan            =\n| number_spans        =\n| piers_in_water      = 2\n| load                =\n| clearance_above     =\n| clearance_below     =\n| life                =\n| architect           =\n| designer            =\n| contracted_designer =\n| winner              =\n| engineering         =PKS Infra Engineers Pvt. Ltd{{cn|date=February 2016}}\n| builder             = [[Reliance Industries Limited]]\n| fabricator          =\n| begin               = 5 May 2011\n| complete            = February 2016\n| cost                = {{INRConvert|7.42|c}}<ref name=\"DeshGujxx2016\"/> \n| open                =\n| inaugurated         ={{start date|11 June 2016}}<ref name=\"DeshGujxx2016\"/>\n| rebuilt             =\n| collapsed           =\n| closed              =\n| replaces            =\n| traffic             =\n| toll                =\n| mapframe_zoom = 14\n}}\n\n'''Sudama Setu''' is a [[pedestrian bridge|pedestrian]] [[suspension bridge]] in [[Dwarka]], [[Gujarat]], India. It is named for [[Sudama]], a childhood friend of [[Krishna]].<ref name=\"PN2015\">{{cite web | author=[[Parimal Nathwani]] | title=Janmashtami and Teacher\u2019s Day Coincides:  Who could be bigger teacher than Krishna? | website=DeshGujarat | date=5 September 2015 | url=http://DeshGujarat.Com/2015/09/05/janmashtami-and-teachers-day-coincides-who-could-be-bigger-teacher-than-krishna/ | accessdate=10 October 2015}}</ref>\n\n==Construction==\nA pedestrian bridge over Gomti river connects [[Dwarkadheesh temple, Gujrat|Jagat Mandir]] of mainland Dwarka and Panchnad or Panchkui Tirth on the island in southeast of it. The bridge was proposed in 2005 to boost tourism on the island. The island has religious as well archaeological significance. There are five sweet water wells called Panchkui associated with five [[Pandava]] brothers of ''[[Mahabharata]]''. Gomti river was crossed by boats until construction of the bridge.<ref name=\"DeshGujaratk2008\">{{cite web | author=DeshGujarat | title=Suspension bridge to link Dwarka and Panchkua island | website=DeshGujarat | date=30 October 2008  | url=http://DeshGujarat.Com/2008/10/30/suspension-bridge-to-link-dwarka-and-panchkua-island/ | accessdate=21 June 2015}}</ref><ref name=\"The Times of Indiak2010\">{{cite web | title=Soon Sudama Setu to connect island to Dwarka temple | website=The Times of India | date=25 June 2010  | url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/rajkot/Soon-Sudama-Setu-to-connect-island-to-Dwarka-temple/articleshow/6089792.cms | accessdate=8 July 2015}}</ref><ref name=\"Indiax2015\">{{cite web | author=India | title=\u2018Sudama setu\u2019 connecting Dwarka with Panchnad likely to be completed before &#91;sic&#93; Janmashtami festival | website=The Indian Express | date=20 June 2015 | url=http://indianexpress.com/article/india/india-others/sudama-setu-connecting-dwarka-with-panchnad-likely-to-be-completed-befor-janmashtami-festival/ | accessdate=21 June 2015}}</ref><ref name=\"dna 2010\">{{cite web | title=Sudama Setu to connect more tourists to Dwarka | website=dna | date=25 June 2010  | url=http://www.dnaindia.com/india/report-sudama-setu-to-connect-more-tourists-to-dwarka-1401014 | accessdate=21 June 2015}}</ref> As Jagat Mandir is an [[Archaeological Survey of India]] (ASI) protected site, permission was needed for construction of the bridge. The Vadodara circle of ASI gave a nod to the bridge in 2008.<ref name=\"DeshGujaratk2008\"/><ref name=\"Indian Express\">{{cite web | title=Suspension bridge to Dwarka gets ASI nod | website=Indian Express | url=http://archive.indianexpress.com/news/suspension-bridge-to-dwarka-gets-asi-nod/377356/ | accessdate=2015-06-21}}</ref> The ground breaking ceremony for the bridge was held on 5 May 2011 by Gujarat Tourism minister [[Jaynarayan Vyas]] and Rajya Sabha MP [[Parimal Nathwani]].<ref name=\"DeshGujarat 2011\">{{cite web | author=DeshGujarat | title=Rs. 9.5 crore Sudama setu project kicks off in Dwarka | website=DeshGujarat | date=5 May 2011  | url=http://DeshGujarat.Com/2011/05/05/rs-9-5-crore-sudama-setu-project-kicks-off-in-dwarka/ | accessdate=21 June 2015}}</ref> Construction of the bridge was delayed due to ASI Delhi not granting the permit until 2013.<ref name=\"www.divyabhaskar.co.in 2013\">{{cite web | title=\u0aa6\u0acd\u0ab5\u0abe\u0ab0\u0a95\u0abe\u0aa8\u0ac0 \u0ab8\u0ac1\u0aa6\u0abe\u0aae\u0abe \u0ab8\u0ac7\u0aa4\u0ac1 \u0aaf\u0acb\u0a9c\u0aa8\u0abe \u0a85\u0aa7\u0acd\u0aa7\u0ab0\u0aa4\u0abe\u0ab2, \u0aa7\u0acb\u0ab7\u0aa3\u0abe \u0aaa\u0acb\u0a95\u0ab3 \u0ab8\u0abe\u0aac\u0abf\u0aa4 \u0aa5\u0a87 | website=www.divyabhaskar.co.in | date=30 May 2013  | url=http://www.divyabhaskar.co.in/news-fb/SAU-JAMN-no-stat-work-on-sudama-setu-plan-4278566-PHO.html | language=gu | accessdate=21 June 2015}}</ref><ref name=\"DeshGujaratbb2011\">{{cite web | author=DeshGujarat | title=Pending ASI approval delaying Sudama Setu project | website=DeshGujarat | date=13 October 2011  | url=http://DeshGujarat.Com/2011/10/13/pending-asi-approval-delaying-sudama-setu-project/ | language=la | accessdate=21 June 2015}}</ref> The bridge was completed in February 2016.<ref name=\"PTI 2016\">{{cite web | author=PTI | title=Construction of 'Sudama Setu' completed in Gujarat | website=The Economic Times | date=1 March 2016 | url=http://economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/economy/infrastructure/construction-of-sudama-setu-completed-in-gujarat/articleshow/51209137.cms | accessdate=5 April 2016}}</ref><ref name=\"Indiax2015\"/><ref name=\"DeshGujarat 2015\">{{cite web | author=DeshGujarat | title=Sudama Setu bridge in Dwarka by July 2015: Minister in Assembly | website=DeshGujarat | date=24 March 2015  | url=http://DeshGujarat.Com/2015/03/24/sudama-setu-bridge-in-dwarka-by-july-2015-minister-in-assembly/ | accessdate=21 June 2015}}</ref><ref name=\"Desh2015\">{{cite web | author=DeshGujarat | title=In photos: Construction of Dwarka Sudama setu almost complete | website=DeshGujarat | date=21 August 2015 | url=http://DeshGujarat.Com/2015/08/21/in-photos-construction-of-dwarka-sudama-setu-almost-complete/ | accessdate=1 September 2015}}</ref>\n\n[[Reliance Industries Limited]], in collaboration with the Gujarat Tourism Department and Gujarat Pavitra Yatradham Vikas Board, built the bridge.<ref name=\"Indiax2015\"/> The bridge cost {{INRConvert|7.42|c}}. It is named for [[Sudama]], a childhood friend of [[Krishna]].<ref name=\"Indiax2015\"/> The bridge is 166 meters long and 4.2 meters wide, having the capacity to carry 25,000 to 30,000 pedestrians an hour.<ref name=\"Indiax2015\"/><ref name=\"DeshGujxx2016\">{{cite web | title=Chief Minister Anandiben Patel Inaugurates \u2018Sudama Setu\u2019 at Dwarka | website=DeshGujarat News from Gujarat | date=11 June 2016 | url=http://deshgujarat.com/2016/06/11/chief-minister-anandiben-patel-inaugurates-sudamasetu-at-dwarka/ | accessdate=23 October 2016}}</ref> The bridge is constructed with 40mm locked coil cable ropes provided by Usha Martin Limited.<ref name=\"Usha Martin 2013\">{{cite web | title=Usha Martin\u2019s bridge cables in Sudama Setu, a cable suspension bridge in Gujarat | website=Usha Martin | date=15 January 2013 | url=http://www.ushamartin.com/news/usha-martins-bridge-cables-in-sudama-setu-a-cable-suspension-bridge-in-gujarat/ | accessdate=10 October 2015}}</ref>\n\nThe bridge was inaugurated by Gujarat Chief Minister [[Anandiben Patel]] on 11 June 2016.<ref name=\"DeshGujxx2016\"/>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n[[Category:Devbhoomi Dwarka district]]\n[[Category:Pedestrian bridges in India]]\n[[Category:Bridges in Gujarat]]\n[[Category:Suspension bridges in India]]\n[[Category:Bridges completed in 2015]]\n[[Category:2015 establishments in India]]\n", "name_user": "Nizil Shah", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sudama_Setu"}
{"title_page": "List of LGBTQ people from New York City", "text_new": "{{Use mdy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{Multiple image\n|header='''''LGBTQ culture in New York City'''''|width=275\n|image1=Stonewall_Inn_5_pride_weekend_2016.jpg|\n|caption1=The [[Stonewall Inn]] in the [[gay village]] of [[Greenwich Village]], [[Manhattan]], the cradle of the modern [[gay rights]] movement.<ref name=GayGreenwichVillage1>{{cite web|url=https://theculturetrip.com/north-america/usa/new-york/articles/why-new-york-city-is-a-major-destination-for-lgbt-travelers/|title=Why New York City Is a Major Destination for LGBT Travelers|author=Julia Goicichea|publisher=The Culture Trip|date=August 16, 2017|accessdate=February 2, 2019}}</ref><ref name=GayGreenwichVillage2>{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2016/06/25/nyregion/stonewall-inn-named-national-monument-a-first-for-gay-rights-movement.html\n|title=Stonewall Inn Named National Monument, a First for the Gay Rights Movement|author=Eli Rosenberg|newspaper=The New York Times|date=June 24, 2016|accessdate=June 25, 2016}}</ref><ref name=GayGreenwichVillage3>{{cite web |url=http://www.nps.gov/diversity/stonewall.htm |title=Workforce Diversity The Stonewall Inn, National Historic Landmark National Register Number: 99000562 |publisher=National Park Service, U.S. Department of the Interior |accessdate=April 21, 2016}}</ref>\n}} \n{{LGBT sidebar}}\nNew York City has one of the largest [[LGBT culture in New York City|LGBTQ]] populations in the world and the most prominent. Brian Silverman, the author of ''Frommer's New York City from $90 a Day,'' wrote the city has \"one of the world's largest, loudest, and most powerful LGBT communities\", and \"Gay and lesbian culture is as much a part of New York's basic identity as [[yellow cab]]s, high-rises, and [[Broadway theater]]\".<ref>Silverman, Brian. ''Frommer's New York City from $90 a Day'' (Volume 7 of Frommer's $ A Day). [[John Wiley & Sons]], January 21, 2005. {{ISBN|0764588354}}, 9780764588358. p. [https://books.google.com/books?id=pZPYLuUnzJ4C&pg=PA28 28].</ref> LGBT Americans in New York City constitute by significant margins the largest self-identifying [[lesbian|'''l'''esbian]], [[gay|'''g'''ay]], [[bisexuality|'''b'''isexual]], and [[transgender|'''t'''ransgender]] communities in the United States, and the 1969 [[Stonewall riots]] in [[Greenwich Village]] are widely considered to be the genesis of the modern [[gay rights]] movement.<ref name=\"StonewallNationalMonument1\">{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2016/06/25/nyregion/stonewall-inn-named-national-monument-a-first-for-gay-rights-movement.html|title=Stonewall Inn Named National Monument, a First for the Gay Rights Movement|author=Eli Rosenberg|newspaper=The New York Times|date=June 24, 2016|accessdate=September 4, 2016}}</ref> As of 2005, New York City was home to an estimated 272,493 self-identifying gay and bisexual individuals.<ref name=GaryGates>{{cite web |url=http://williamsinstitute.law.ucla.edu/wp-content/uploads/Gates-Same-Sex-Couples-GLB-Pop-ACS-Oct-2006.pdf |title=Same-sex Couples and the Gay, Lesbian, Bisexual Population: New Estimates from the American Community Survey |author=Gary J. Gates |date=October 2006 |publisher=The Williams Institute |accessdate=September 4, 2016}}</ref> The [[New York City metropolitan area]] had an estimated 568,903 self-identifying GLB residents.<ref name=GaryGates/> Meanwhile, New York City is also home to the largest transgender population in the United States, estimated at 50,000 in 2018, concentrated in [[Manhattan]] and [[Queens]].<ref name=NYCTrans>{{cite news|url=https://www.timesledger.com/stories/2016/48/transvigil_2016_11_25_q.html|title=Elmhurst vigil remembers transgender victims lost to violence and hate|author=Bill Parry|newspaper=Daily News|location=New York|date=July 10, 2018|accessdate=November 11, 2018}}</ref> The following represents a list of notable self-identified LGBTQ New Yorkers.\n\n==List of notable self-identified LGBTQ New Yorkers==\n<!---  Please alphabetize correctly and copy-paste the correct hyphen.  --->\n{{Image frame|width=354|content= \u2212 <gallery mode=packed heights=100 style=\"width:350px; background:#fafafa;font-size:85%; line-height:130%;\">\nFile:Acid Betty at RuPaul's Dragcon 2017 by dvsross (2).jpg|[[Acid Betty]]\nFile:Desiree Akhavan 2015-05-24.png|[[Desiree Akhavan]]\nFile:J. Alexander 2014 cropped.jpg|[[J. Alexander (model)|J. Alexander]]\nFile:Michael Alig 2015.jpg|[[Michael Alig]]\nFile:Nahshon_Anderson.jpg|[[Nahshon Dion Anderson]]\nFile:Aquaria, drag queen, 2018.jpg|[[Aquaria (drag queen)|Aquaria]]\nFile:Arden, Michael (2006).jpg|[[Michael Arden]]\nFile:Joey Arias 2009 Howl Festival 1 by DS.jpg|[[Joey Arias]]\nFile:Ellis Avery Author Photo, 2011.jpg|[[Ellis Avery]]\nFile:Fierce Hiro at the Maritime Hotel 20070910.10D.45792 SML (1389640840).jpg|[[Kevin Aviance]]\nFile:Cardi B - Openair Frauenfeld 2019 02.jpg|[[Cardi B]]\nFile:Josh Barro.jpg|[[Josh Barro]]\nFile:James Beard.jpg|[[James Beard]]\nFile:Sandra Bernhard crop.JPG|[[Sandra Bernhard]]\nFile:Mykki Blanco Performing in 2017.jpg|[[Mykki Blanco]]\nFile:Charles blow 2014.jpg|[[Charles Blow]]\nFile:Mal Blum June 2015.JPG|[[Mal Blum]]\nFile:Bob The Drag Queen at Rupaul's Dragcon 2017 by dvsross.jpg|[[Bob The Drag Queen]]\nFile:Matt Bomer Comic-con by Gage Skidmore.jpg|[[Matt Bomer]]\nFile:Keith Boykin 2017.jpg|[[Keith Boykin]]\nFile:Lady Bunny 2001.jpg|[[Lady Bunny]]\nFile:Augusten Burroughs by David Shankbone.jpg|[[Augusten Burroughs]]\nFile:David Burtka 2012.jpg|[[David Burtka]]\nFile:Regie cabico 4192049.JPG|[[Regie Cabico]]\nFile:Rupaul Dragcon 2018-306 (41377493474).jpg|[[Jiggly Caliente]]\nFile:Candis Cayne.jpg|[[Candis Cayne]]\nFile:Cazwell 2015.jpg|[[Cazwell]]\nFile:Andy Cohen at Digitas NewFront 2012 (7116540321) (cropped).jpg|[[Andy Cohen (television personality)|Andy Cohen]]\nFile:Jenn Colella Gimme A Break 2012.jpg|[[Jenn Colella]]\nFile:Anderson Cooper at Tulane University.jpg|[[Anderson Coope