opped.jpg|[[Randi Weingarten]]\nFile:Rutina Wesley by Gage Skidmore.jpg|[[Rutina Wesley]]\nFile:Edmund White 2 by David Shankbone.jpg|[[Edmund White]]\nFile:Walt Whitman - George Collins Cox.jpg|[[Walt Whitman]]\nFile:Samira Wiley 13.jpg|[[Samira Wiley]]\nFile:Jenna Wolfe chatting with people (cropped).jpg|[[Jenna Wolfe]]\nFile:Jason Wu Shankbone 2009 Metropolitan Opera.jpg|[[Jason Wu]]\n</gallery>\n|caption='''Self-identifying LGBTQ New Yorkers'''\n}}\n\n===Academia and research===\n* [[Andrew Dolkart]] \u2013 co-founder, NYC LGBT Historic Sites Project; professor, [[historic preservation]], [[Columbia University Graduate School of Architecture|Columbia University Graduate School of Architecture, Planning and Preservation]] (GSAPP)<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.columbia.edu/news/digital-project-maps-sites-new-yorks-lgbt-history|title=A Digital Project Maps the Sites of New York's LGBT History &#124; Columbia News|website=news.columbia.edu}}</ref>\n* [[Kevin Nadal]] \u2013 professor of [[psychology]] and researcher at [[John Jay College of Criminal Justice]] and [[The Graduate Center, CUNY|The Graduate Center]] of the [[City University of New York]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.jjay.cuny.edu/faculty/kevin-l-nadal|title=Kevin L. Nadal|website=John Jay College of Criminal Justice}}</ref>\n* [[Marcia Pally]] \u2013 professor at [[New York University | NYU]], author, co-founder and former acting chair of [[GLAAD]]<ref>[https://archive.org/details/gaycommunitynews1432gayc/page/2/mode/2up/search/Pally?q=%22MArcia+Pally%22 ''Politics of Ego: GLAAD Saga Unravelled'', Gay Community News, p.3 (March 1\u20137, 1987)]</ref>\n\n===Entrepreneurship and technology===\n* [[Eva Kotchever]] \u2013 founder of [[Eve's Hangout]] in Greenwich Village, deported to Europe and assassinated at [[Auschwitz]].<ref>https://www.atlasobscura.com/articles/what-was-first-gay-bar</ref>\n* [[Bradford Shellhammer]] \u2013 entrepreneur and designer, founding editor of ''[[Queerty]]''<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.out.com/out-exclusives/wedding-guide/vows/2013/04/12/bradford-shellhammer-georgi-balinov|title=Bradford Shellhammer & Georgi Balinov|date=April 12, 2013|website=out.com}}</ref>\n* [[Joel Spolsky]] \u2013 software engineer<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cityandstateny.com/articles/special-list/new-york-2019-pride-power-100-6-35.html|title=The 2019 Pride Power 100; 6 \u2013 35|date=June 23, 2019|website=CSNY}}</ref>\n\n===Fashion===\n{{see also|New York Fashion Week}}\n\n====Design====\n* [[Thom Browne]] \u2013 fashion designer<ref name=\"auto5\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2016/05/01/nyregion/how-andrew-bolton-of-met-costume-institute-spends-his-sundays.html|title=How Andrew Bolton of Met Costume Institute Spends His Sundays|first=John|last=Leland|date=April 29, 2016|newspaper=The New York Times}}</ref>\n* [[Drew Elliott]] \u2013 creative director and [[creative consultant|consultant]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://fashionweekdaily.com/christian-cowan-fall-2019/|title=Christian Cowan Mines His Wild and Crazy Club-Kid Past For Fall 2019|date=February 13, 2019|website=Daily Front Row}}</ref>\n* [[Prabal Gurung]] \u2013 fashion designer<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://myrepublica.nagariknetwork.com/news/52389/|title=I am gay and proud to be one: Prabal Gurung|first=Kiran|last=Lama|website=My City}}</ref>\n* [[Marc Jacobs]] \u2013 fashion designer<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/life-style/love-sex/marc-jacobs-proposal-boyfriend-flash-mob-chipotle-char-defrancesco-new-york-a8289881.html|title=Marc Jacobs proposes to boyfriend using a flashmob and it is spectacular|date=April 5, 2018|website=The Independent}}</ref>\n* [[Calvin Klein]] \u2013 fashion designer<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/hannahelliott/2011/10/18/calvin-klein-on-kate-moss-ralph-lauren-love-and-other-drugs/|title=Calvin Klein On Kate Moss, Ralph Lauren, Love And Other Drugs|first=Hannah|last=Elliott|website=Forbes}}</ref>\n* [[Michael Kors]] \u2013 fashion designer<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cbsnews.com/news/designer-michael-kors-marries-longtime-partner/|title=Designer Michael Kors marries longtime partner|publisher=CBS News}}</ref>\n* [[Derek Lam]] \u2013 fashion designer<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.wsj.com/articles/derek-lam-expands-his-apparel-line-1417717017|title=Derek Lam Expands His Apparel Line|first=Emily|last=Holt|date=December 4, 2014|newspaper=The Wall Street Journal}}</ref>\n* [[Humberto Leon]] \u2013 fashion designer<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://blog.openingceremony.com/entry.asp?pid=9789|title=Father's Day: A Personal Essay From Humberto Leon \u2013 OPENING CEREMONY|website=blog.openingceremony.com}}</ref>\n* [[Phillip Lim]] \u2013 fashion designer<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.fastcompany.com/1777619/phillip-lim-we-live-dress-we-die-dress|title=Phillip Lim: \"We Live By The Dress, We Die By The Dress\"|first=Bee-Shyuan|last=Chang|date=September 14, 2011|publisher=Fast Company}}</ref>\n* [[Isaac Mizrahi]] \u2013 fashion designer<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/outlook/i-stuck-out-like-a-chubby-gay-thumb-isaac-mizrahi-on-his-childhood--and-his-escape/2019/03/08/a8066156-289f-11e9-b2fc-721718903bfc_story.html|title=Review &#124; 'I stuck out like a chubby gay thumb': Isaac Mizrahi on his childhood \u2013 and his escape|first=Karen Iris|last=Tucker|website=The Washington Post}}</ref>\n* [[Zac Posen]] \u2013 fashion designer<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.voanews.com/arts-culture/zac-posen-comeback-kid-featured-new-documentary|title=Zac Posen, The Comeback Kid, Featured in New Documentary|publisher=Voice of America}}</ref>\n* [[Christian Siriano]] \u2013 fashion designer<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.observer.com/2008/nightlife-photographer-brad-walsh-presents-debut-photo-show|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080310131909/http://www.observer.com/2008/nightlife-photographer-brad-walsh-presents-debut-photo-show|url-status=dead|archive-date=March 10, 2008|title=Project Runway Winner's BF Unveils Nightlife Photos\u2014in Park Slope! &#124; The New York Observer|date=March 10, 2008}}</ref>\n* [[Alexander Wang (designer)|Alexander Wang]] \u2013 fashion designer<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2016/06/23/fashion/my-first-gay-bar-rosie-odonnell-rachel-maddow-alexander-wang-andy-cohen-share.html|title='My First Gay Bar': Rachel Maddow, Andy Cohen and Others Share Their Coming-Out Stories|date=June 22, 2016|work=The New York Times}}</ref>\n* [[Jason Wu]] \u2013 fashion designer<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.taipeitimes.com/News/feat/archives/2016/04/24/2003644676|title=Taipei Watcher: 'Taiwan's glory' marries same-sex partner \u2013 Taipei Times|website=Taipei Times}}</ref>\n\n====Modeling====\n* [[J. Alexander (model)|J. Alexander]] \u2013 [[fashion model|model]] and fashion designer<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.usmagazine.com/celebrity-moms/news/watch-top-models-miss-j-reveal-hes-a-dad-20091011/|title=Watch Top Model's \"Miss J\" Reveal He's a Dad!|date=November 10, 2009}}</ref>\n* [[Leyna Bloom]] \u2013 fashion model and transgender activist<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.out.com/film/2019/4/18/leyna-bloom-port-authority-cannes-premiere|title=Meet Leyna Bloom, First Trans Woman of Color to Lead a Cannes Premiere|date=April 18, 2019|website=out.com}}</ref>\n* [[Cara Delevingne]] \u2013 supermodel and actress<ref name=DelvingneBensonNYC>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cosmopolitan.com/uk/entertainment/a22733856/cara-delevingne-ashley-benson-relationship-timeline/|title=No, Cara Delevingne and Ashley Benson haven't broken up|first=Naomi|last=Gordon|date=December 10, 2019|website=Cosmopolitan}}</ref>\n* [[Peche Di]] \u2013 transgender model, who started the first transgender modeling agency in the U.S., in New York City<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.huffpost.com/entry/the-trans-model-agency-is-working-to-mainstream-trans-beauty_n_56b8ca55e4b08069c7a81d10|title=The Trans Modeling Agency Is on a Mission To Mainstream Trans Beauty|firs