 George Dorris|date=July 23, 2006|work=The New York Times}}</ref>\n* [[Rose Arce]] \u2013 journalist and producer<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cnn.com/2013/06/26/living/same-sex-marriage-rose-arce/index.html|title=Same-sex marriage: The only history that counts for me is my own|first=Rose |last=Arce|publisher=CNN}}</ref>\n* [[Josh Barro]] \u2013 journalist and senior editor, ''[[Business Insider]]''<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.out.com/out-exclusives/out100-2014/2014/11/10/out100-journalists-chris-geidner-sewell-chan-masha-gessen-josh|title=OUT100: Journalists Chris Geidner, Sewell Chan, Masha Gessen & Josh Barro|date=November 10, 2014|website=out.com}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.salon.com/2013/03/26/dont_you_dare_delete_josh_barro_wikipedia/|title=Don't you dare delete Josh Barro, Wikipedia!|date=March 26, 2013|website=Salon}}</ref>\n* [[Charles Blow]] \u2013 visual [[op-ed]] columnist, ''[[The New York Times]]''<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.huffpost.com/entry/charles-blow-bisexual-_n_5885408|title=Charles Blow On His Lifelong Struggles With Identifying As Bisexual|date=September 26, 2014|website=HuffPost}}</ref>\n* [[Keith Boykin]] \u2013 [[print syndication|syndicated columnist]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/keithboykin/status/815229534366826497?lang=en|title=I'm a black gay man. Please tell Kim Burrell that religion should be used as a tool for love, not a weapon of hate. |first=Keith|last=Boykin|date=December 31, 2016}}{{Primary source inline|date=April 2020}}</ref>\n* [[Ben Brantley]] \u2013 journalist and chief theater critic,''[[The New York Times]]''<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.americantheatre.org/2017/03/24/jesse-green-is-looking-for-a-good-argument/|title=Jesse Green Is Looking for a Good Argument|first=Rob|last=Weinert-Kendt|date=March 24, 2017|website=AMERICAN THEATRE}}</ref>\n* [[Frank Bruni]] \u2013 journalist and op-ed columnist, ''[[The New York Times]]''<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.out.com/entertainment/2008/10/29/our-boys-bus|title=Our Boys on the Bus|date=October 29, 2008|website=out.com}}</ref>\n* [[Sam Champion]] \u2013 [[meteorologist]] and [[weather forecasting|television weather anchor]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/life/people/2012/12/21/sam-champion-marries-partner-ruben-robierb/1785985/|title='GMA' anchor Sam Champion marries his partner|website=USA Today}}</ref>\n* [[Andy Cohen (television personality)|Andy Cohen]] \u2013 television personality<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/life/entertainthis/2018/12/31/andy-cohen-reveals-baby-boy-cnn-new-years-special/2456032002/|title=Andy Cohen reveals he's having a baby boy on CNN New Year's Eve special|first=Bryan|last=Alexander|website=USA Today}}</ref>\n* [[Anderson Cooper]] \u2013 journalist and television [[anchorman|anchor]], ''[[CNN]]''<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://mediadecoder.blogs.nytimes.com/2012/07/02/anderson-cooper-says-the-fact-is-im-gay/|title=Revelation Signals a Shift in Views of Homosexuality|first=Brian|last=Stelter|date=July 2, 2012}}</ref>\n* [[Angela Dimayuga]] \u2013 [[food critic]] for ''The New York Times'',<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.sfgate.com/food/article/Mission-Chinese-Food-Angela-Dimayuga-interview-11074014.php|title=Chef turns down interview for Ivanka Trump site with strongly worded response|date=April 14, 2017|website=San Francisco Chronicle}}</ref> chef\n* [[George Dorris]] \u2013 editor and writer<ref name=\"auto4\"/>\n* [[David W. Dunlap]] \u2013 journalist, ''The New York Times''<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2017/06/19/us/gay-pride-lgbtq-new-york-times.html|title=How The Times Gave 'Gay' Its Own Voice (Again)|first=David W.|last=Dunlap|date=June 19, 2017|work=The New York Times}}</ref>\n* [[Ronan Farrow]] \u2013 journalist and lawyer<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.advocate.com/news/2019/10/16/ronan-farrow-proposed-jon-lovett-draft-catch-and-kill|title=Ronan Farrow Proposed to Jon Lovett in a Draft of 'Catch and Kill'|date=October 16, 201