z |first=Rafaella |website=gaystarnews.com |publisher=Gay Star News |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190730201958/https://www.gaystarnews.com/article/herstory-trans-women-rupauls-drag-race/ |archive-date=July 30, 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n* [[Miz Cracker]] \u2013 drag queen (contestant on the tenth season of ''RuPaul's Drag Race'')<ref name=\"cracker\">{{cite web |url=https://werrrk.com/11857-2/ |title=Help Miz Cracker Help the LGBT Community of Uganda! |date=June 29, 2016 |last=Dior |first=Chiffon |access-date=November 11, 2019 |website=Werrrk.com |publisher=MH Magazine |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190219020159/https://werrrk.com/11857-2/ |archive-date=February 19, 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n* [[Honey Davenport]] \u2013 activist, singer, and drag queen (contestant on the eleventh season of ''RuPaul's Drag Race'')<ref name=\"root\">{{cite news |url=https://www.theroot.com/rupauls-drag-race-contestant-honey-davenport-shares-why-1835271989 |title=''RuPaul's Drag Race'' Contestant Honey Davenport Shares Why the Art of Drag Is Revolutionary |last=Townsend |first=Corey |date=June 5, 2019 |access-date=June 7, 2019 |magazine=[[The Root (magazine)|The Root]]  |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190607003126/https://www.theroot.com/rupauls-drag-race-contestant-honey-davenport-shares-why-1835271989 |archive-date=June 7, 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n* [[Sahara Davenport]] \u2013 late singer and drag queen (contestant on the [[RuPaul's Drag Race (season 2)|second season]] of ''RuPaul's Drag Race'')<ref name=\"sahara\">{{cite news |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/sahara-davenport-rupauls-drag-race-376210 |title='RuPaul's Drag Race' Contestant Sahara Davenport Dies at 27 |last=Schillaci |first=Sophie |date=October 3, 2012 |access-date=November 12, 2019 |magazine=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] |publisher=Lynne Segall |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180826214410/https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/sahar