lee (TV series)|Glee]]\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.afterelton.com/people/2009/10/jonathan-groff-out|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120531032652/http://www.afterelton.com/people/2009/10/jonathan-groff-out|url-status=dead|archive-date=May 31, 2012|title=Tony Award Nominee Jonathan Groff has Most Low-key Coming Out Ever. &#124; AfterElton.com|date=May 31, 2012}}</ref>\n* [[Jeremy O. Harris]] \u2013 actor and playwright<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.out.com/out-exclusives/2018/11/08/meet-jeremy-oharris-queer-black-savior-theater-world-needs|title=Meet Jeremy O. Harris: The Queer Black Savior the Theater World Needs|date=November 8, 2018|website=out.com}}</ref>\n* [[Neil Patrick Harris]] \u2013 Broadway and television actor, producer, singer, comedian, [[magician (paranormal)|magician]], and television host<ref name=\"auto\"/>\n* [[Brian Hutchison]] \u2013 actor<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.indiewire.com/2019/04/boys-in-the-band-ryan-murphy-showtime-1202059745/|title=Ryan Murphy to Bring Controversial Gay Play 'The Boys in the Band' to Netflix|first1=Jude|last1=Dry|first2=Jude|last2=Dry|date=April 17, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.lct.org/explore/blog/brian-hutchison-love-math-music/|title=Brian Hutchison on Love, Math, Music|first=Lincoln Center|last=Theater|website=Lincoln Center Theater}}</ref>\n* [[Cheyenne Jackson]] \u2013 actor and singer<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.advocate.com/news/daily-news/2011/09/03/just-married-cheyenne-jackson-weds-longtime-partner-new-york|archiveurl=https://archive.today/20120721023552/http://www.advocate.com/news/daily-news/2011/09/03/just-married-cheyenne-jackson-weds-longtime-partner-new-york|archive-date=July 21, 2012|url-status=dead|title=Just Married Cheyenne Jackson Weds Longtime Partner in New York|date=September 3, 2011|website=advocate.com|access-date=October 20, 2019}}</ref>\n* [[Larry Kramer]] \u2013 playwright, author, producer, and LGBT rights advocate<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.yalealumn