moirist<ref name=\"auto2\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.pshares.org/issues/spring-1999/about-mark-doty-profile|title=About Mark Doty: A Profile &#124; Ploughshares|website=Ploughshares}}</ref>\n* [[Martin Duberman]] \u2013 biographer and historian<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://forward.com/culture/323491/martin-dubermans-radical-85-year-journey-through-white-america/|title=Martin Duberman's Radical 85-Year Journey Through White America|website=The Forward}}</ref>\n* [[Grace Dunham]] \u2013 author<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.konbini.com/en/lifestyle/grace-dunham-gender-project/|title=Grace Dunham Lifts The Lid On Being Non-Binary in a Privileged World|website=Konbini \u2013 All Pop Everything!}}</ref>\n* [[David Ebershoff]] \u2013 author and editor<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2018/11/05/t-magazine/gay-male-ballet-dancers.html|title=How a Group of Gay Male Ballet Dancers Is Rethinking Masculinity|first=David|last=Ebershoff|date=November 5, 2018|work=The New York Times}}</ref>\n* [[Allen Ginsberg]] \u2013 late poet, philosopher, and writer<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://gvshp.org/blog/2017/01/09/lgbt-history-not-just-west-village-bars/|title=LGBT History: Not Just West Village Bars|first=Matthew|last=Morowitz|date=January 9, 2017}}</ref>\n* [[Paul Lisicky]] \u2013 author and memoirist<ref name=\"auto2\"/>\n* [[Jaime Manrique]] \u2013 poet, essayist, and translator<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.gaycitynews.nyc/stories/2019/12/jaime-manrique-books-2019-06-06-gcn.html|title=Colombia's Gay Truth Teller|website=Gay City News}}</ref>\n* [[Eric Marcus]] \u2013 author<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.nbcnews.com/feature/nbc-out/pride50-eric-marcus-lgbtq-historian-n1008106|title=#Pride50: LGBTQ historian Eric Marcus|publisher=NBC News}}</ref>\n* [[Darnell L. Moore]] \u2013 author<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2018/08/08/books/review/darnell-l-moore-no-ashes-in-the-fire.html|title=Black, Gay and Becoming Visible|first=Ijeoma|last=Oluo|date=August 8, 2018|work